    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER SERIES - INSTALL - REAR HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="9">
        <title>REAR HOUSING</title>
        <para>Position rear housing on the dowel pins (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13025i2">Figure 182</hotlnk>) and install bolts (inset). Tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to
            61 N&#183; m).
        </para>
        <figure id="f13025i2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025i2" filename="../figg13/G13025i2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 182. Position Rear Housing on Dowel Pins and Install Bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged driver to install the output shaft bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025i3">Figure 183</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Pick up on the output shaft to help start the rear bearing in the bore.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f13025i3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025i3" filename="../figg13/G13025i3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 183. Install Output Shaft Bearing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert rear countershafts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025i4">Figure 184</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13025i4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025i4" filename="../figg13/G13025i4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 184. Install Rear Countershafts</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When installing the upper countershaft, pick up on the first speed gear. This will aid in aligning
                    the shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13025i4">inset</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">In models so equipped, install snap rings in the groove of the rear countershafts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025i5">Figure 185</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13025i5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025i5" filename="../figg13/G13025i5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 185. Install Snap Rings in Groove of Rear Countershafts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged driver to install the rear countershaft bearings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025i6">Figure 186</hotlnk>) and retaining snap rings (inset).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13025i6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025i6" filename="../figg13/G13025i6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 186. Install Rear Countershaft Bearings and Retaining Snap Rings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the output shaft spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025i7">Figure 187</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13025i7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025i7" filename="../figg13/G13025i7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 187. Install Output Shaft Spacer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If previously removed, install the oil seal in the rear bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025i8">left, Figure 188</hotlnk>). Seal should be installed so the spring is to the
                front of the cover (right).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13025i8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025i8" filename="../figg13/G13025i8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 188. Install Oil Seal With Spring to Front of Rear Bearing Cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align rear bearing cover oil return hole with the hole in the rear housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025i9">Figure 189</hotlnk>). Install rear cover bolts (inset). Tighten to 35 to 45
                ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13025i9" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025i9" filename="../figg13/G13025i9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 189. Align Rear Bearing Cover Oil Return Hole With Hole in Rear Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install countershaft rear bearing covers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025j0">Figure 190</hotlnk>). Tighten bolts to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13025j0" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025j0" filename="../figg13/G13025j0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 190. Install Countershaft Rear Bearing Covers</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
